Program: Outlook
Title: 03/03/2010
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p006dg52
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 4 Mar 2010
Personal stories behind the news from all over the world. With Matthew Bannister. South Africa's trafficked children, Jordanian royal insider,Hong Kong's film fixer. South Africa's trafficked children. With less than a hundred days to go to the World Cup in South Africa fears grow that the event will lead to more child trafficking. Already on the rise, NGO's warn more must be done to protect vulnerable children in the region. Jordanian Royal Insider. Lebanese journalist Randa Habib has been based in Jordan for the last twenty-five years. Her close friendship with the late King Hussein gave her unprecedented access to the leading political figures of the time. Her special status meant she was often part of the story as well as reporting on it. Hong Kong Film Fixer. We meet the fixer who oils the wheels of international movie making in Hong Kong Show less